{{Politics of Bahrain}} The '''National Action Charter of Bahrain''' is a document put forward by King [[Hamad ibn Isa Al Khalifah]] of [[Bahrain]] in 2001 in order to end the popular [[1990s Uprising]] and return the country to constitutional rule. It was approved in a national referendum in 2001, in which 98.4% of the voters voted in favor of the document.
==Referendum== The referendum took place on 14 and 15 February. Voter turnout was 90.2%, with 98.41% voting in favour.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=sWAEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT25 Bahrain: Referendum on Government Structure] Elections Today, Spring 2001, p26</ref><ref name="UNDP-POGAR">{{cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =Country Theme: Elections: Bahrain| work =| publisher =[[United Nations Development Program|UNDP]]-Programme on Governance in the Arab Region| year =2011| url =http://www.pogar.org/countries/theme.aspx?t=3&cid=2 |format =| doi =| accessdate =2011-02-09 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wNSNDw42 |archivedate=2011-02-09 |deadurl=no }}</ref>
